## Purpose

Define the mandatory process for creating any new UI component — whether LD primitive or WCP product-level. This rule ensures consistency, avoids duplication, and guarantees every component is documented, sandboxed, and theme-compliant.

---

## Pre-Creation Checklist (MANDATORY)

Before writing a single line of code, complete these checks:

- [ ] **Search existing components** in `client/components/ui/` (LD primitives) and `client/components/walmart/` (WCP components)
- [ ] **Search all 303+ icons** at `/component-library#icons`
- [ ] **Check guideline docs** in `guidelines/components/` for existing specs
- [ ] **Verify no duplicates exist** — grep for similar names and functionality
- [ ] **Determine LD vs WCP** — see decision tree below

**Priority: Reuse > Adapt > Create**

If a similar component exists, extend it with a new variant or compose it — do not create a duplicate.

---

## Decision Tree — LD or WCP?

```
Is this a general-purpose design primitive (Button, Input, Tag, Spinner)?
  └─ YES → LD Component (client/components/ui/)
           Follow RULE_CreateNewComponent.mdc (10-step process)

Is this a Walmart-specific product component (Banner, Card, Tile, Carousel)?
  └─ YES → WCP Component (client/components/walmart/)
           Follow RULE_WCPComponentCreation.mdc (lightweight process)
```

When in doubt: if it contains business logic, Walmart copy, or is only used in Walmart pages → WCP.

