## File Naming Conventions

| File type | Convention | Example |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Component | PascalCase | `MyComponent.tsx` |
| CSS module | PascalCase (match component) | `MyComponent.module.css` |
| Custom icons | PascalCase in `icons-custom/` | `MyIcon.tsx` |

Never add files to `client/components/icons/` — that is the core LD library. Custom icons go in `client/components/icons-custom/`.

---

## Component File Structure

### Required Exports

- **Named exports only** — never `export default` for components
- Export the component function and its props interface
- Export variant type unions for consumer use

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
export type MyComponentVariant = 'default' | 'brand' | 'inverse';

export interface MyComponentProps {
  variant?: MyComponentVariant;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function MyComponent({ variant = 'default', children }: MyComponentProps) {
  return <div className={[styles.root, styles[variant]].filter(Boolean).join(' ')}>{children}</div>;
}

// ❌ WRONG
export default function MyComponent() { ... }
```

### Props Design Rules

| Rule | Example |
|------|---------|
| String union types for variants — never enums | `type Variant = 'small' \| 'medium' \| 'large'` |
| Optional with sensible defaults | `variant?: Variant` (default in destructuring) |
| `UNSAFE_className` for escape hatches | `UNSAFE_className?: string` |
| `UNSAFE_style` for dynamic overrides | `UNSAFE_style?: React.CSSProperties` |
| `children` for slot content | `children: React.ReactNode` |
| `aria-label` for accessibility | `'aria-label'?: string` |

### Variant Class Composition

Always use array join — never switch/if chains:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
className={[styles.root, styles[variant], styles[size]].filter(Boolean).join(' ')}

// ❌ WRONG
let cls = styles.root;
if (variant === 'brand') cls += ' ' + styles.brand;
```

