## CSS Module Requirements

### Semantic Tokens Only (Zero Exceptions)

```css
/* ✅ CORRECT */
.root {
  background: var(--ld-semantic-color-surface, #fff);
  color: var(--ld-semantic-color-text, #2e2f32);
  padding: var(--ld-primitive-scale-space-300, 12px);
  border-radius: var(--ld-primitive-scale-borderradius-100, 8px);
  font-family: var(--ld-semantic-font-family-sans);
}

/* ❌ WRONG */
.root {
  background: #ffffff;
  color: #2e2f32;
  padding: 12px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-family: 'Everyday Sans UI';
}
```

### Responsive Breakpoints (Standard Set)

Every component with layout must handle these breakpoints:

| Breakpoint | Target | Padding |
|------------|--------|---------|
| `> 1024px` | Desktop | `24px–32px` |
| `≤ 1024px` | Tablet | `20px–24px` |
| `≤ 768px` | Small tablet | `16px` |
| `≤ 480px` | Phone | `12px` |

### Motion Accessibility

Every animation or transition MUST include:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .animated {
    animation: none;
    transition: none;
  }
}
```

### Separator vs Border Tokens

- **Dividers / separators**: `var(--ld-semantic-color-separator, #e3e4e5)`
- **Interactive borders** (inputs, card frames): `var(--ld-semantic-color-border-subtle)`

Never use `border-subtle` for divider lines.

