## Post-Creation Checklist (MANDATORY)

After creating the component, you MUST complete all of these:

- [ ] **Component library page** — create or update a page under `client/pages/component-library/`
- [ ] **Route in App.tsx** — register lazy import + route
- [ ] **Sidebar entry** — add to `ComponentLibraryLayout.tsx` navigation
- [ ] **Overview.tsx entry** — add card to component overview
- [ ] **i18n keys** — add `nav` + `desc` keys to all 3 locale files (en, es, fr)
- [ ] **Sandbox entry** — add to `ComponentTester.tsx` if the component has interactive props
- [ ] **Theme compliance** — verify with Bodega + Legacy themes, zero hardcoded hex in CSS
- [ ] **Accessibility** — keyboard nav, focus states, aria attributes, never disable buttons

### Theme Compliance Verification

```bash
# Must return 0 results for your component's CSS file:
grep -n "#[0-9a-fA-F]\{6\}" client/components/walmart/MyComponent.module.css
grep -n "ld-primitive-color-" client/components/walmart/MyComponent.module.css
```

---

## Grouping Similar Components

When creating a component that is a variant of an existing pattern, add it to the existing component library page rather than creating a new one:

| New component | Add to existing page |
|---------------|---------------------|
| New item tile variant | Item Tile page |
| New carousel type | Carousels & Product Grids page |
| New banner variant | Promo Banners page |
| New order card variant | Order & Status Cards page |
| New dropdown type | Dropdowns page |

Only create a new page when the component represents a genuinely new pattern.

